There's something ever so appealing about the stark contrast within black and white photographs. The surrounding white snow and a single subject out in the distance. It's a tableau of exploration and caution, of the thrill of the journey and the responsibility we carry. As we carve paths into the untouched, let's remember to tread lightly, for we are visitors in nature's grand design. 
Still thinking of winter, but damn am I ready for summer.

Dinosaurs of the deep, emerging from the darkness to check out what all is going on at the surface - only to realize it's merely a bunch of humans splashing around and not a tasty treat. 
Shark behavior is such a fascinating thing to witness and never ceases to amaze me every time I'm in the water. Millions of years of refinement jam packed into these incredible apex predators.
Kauai, you truly are one of a kind.
